Quote:  ... I doubt if any more pleasing sight could have been met up with along the whole length of the ranges at Christmas time than the old whare, when that most beautiful of our native flowers, the scarlet mistletoe, is hanging in festoons from the sombre beeches that encircle the glade.
Notes:

Date: 0/9/2002
Source: NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page: No. 59/8
Edition:
Quote: ... a spray of scarlet mistletoe, Peraxilla colensoi, was chosen to grace our former $2 note - the only time a threatened plant has been depicted on our currency. This note is now a relic, and scarlet mistletoe, in common with several of our other native mistletoes, is in danger of following suit. <i>Ibid.</i> 88Scarlet mistletoe, or korukoru (<i>Peraxilla colensoi</i>), can be found in forests that support healthy populations of silver beech at a number of sites throughout the South Island and as far north as Tongariro.
